====Usage notes====
* Like Modern French {{m|fr|tout}}, when used as an intensifier it may inflect according to the gender and the number of what it is describing:
*: {{ux|frm|Elle est '''toute''' morte|t=she is completely dead|inline=1}}
* The uninflected form ''tout'' is always used for describing terms that don't inflect with gender, such as verbs, adverbs and prepositions:
*: {{ux|frm|y avoit de gens '''tout''' autour|t=there were people all around|inline=1}} (''tout'' qualifies the preposition {{m|frm|autour}})

